CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper June 30, 1945, pg. 22, reads: "President Ten Years - Mrs. E. M. King was honored last Thursday evening at Ebenezer Baptist Church by the Woman's Auxiliary to the Pennsylvania State Baptist Convention. Mrs. King has completed ten years of outstanding service as its president, and eighteen years as head of the Western District. Nearly 300 attended the affair. In the picture, left to right: Mrs. Flora Marshall of Philadelphia, Miss Dorothy Guinn, Mrs. E. M. King, Mrs. Homer S. Brown and Mrs. Ella Williams, general chairman. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Flora Marshall, Dorothy Guinn, E. M. King, Wilhelmina "Billie" Byrd Brown and Ella Williams posed behind table in Ebenezer Baptist Church
